parameters:
Are you going out? Take care, dear. Please give my regards
to Kotarou-dono.

Last night was fun, wasn't it? It seems Karin was also
satisfied.
Good morning, Korin. About... last night, I'm sorry...

No... You've been busy these past three months, so why not
take a break for a while?

That's true. How about we go to a hidden hot spring nearby
with the family before it gets fully into winter? Karin
would be delighted, I'm sure.

Yes, let's do that. I will ask Koutarou-dono for permission
to leave the village.

It's another beautiful day today. Let's go to the hot
springs before it gets cold.
This treasured sword—it still glows as always.

At night, when drawn, it serves as a light source. Quite
convenient and saves on oil too.

Originally, it was the sword that Karin brought with her
when she fled... It seems true that it's a treasured sword
passed down through generations. The blade glows a pale
blue, truly an eerie sword.

The demon-slaying divine weapon—it was once called that, but
now even its true name has been lost. It's a precious sword
never to leave the family, so my grandmother said she
inherited it but never actually used it.

There's no way to test it since demons don't actually exist.
However, I feel something unfathomable with this sword. I
must cherish it and continue to pass it down in honor of
Karin's ancestors—
--The treasured sword is glowing pale blue...

Karin-chan really loves playing the pellet drum. She gets so
happy. Fufu♪

Good morning, Nakatarou-sama. You seemed to be quite
exhausted.

Indeed... I didn't overexert myself, but it seems my body
was tired from the long journey. I slept soundly, feeling
safe at home.

It's been a while, Uncle Nakatarou. You must be tired from
your espionage mission.

Oh, Momiji? It's been three months, hasn't it? I'm glad to
see you after such a long time.

You came to take care of Karin again today. It's truly a
blessing to have someone help with child-rearing.

When I was a child, you always took care of me, so this is
my way of returning the favor. Plus, Karin-chan has grown
quite fond of me... right, Karin-chan?

I've heard that you took good care of Karin while I was
away. I am grateful to you, Momiji.

No... And so, my father Kotarou would like to hear about the
situation in the capital and has asked for you to come to
the mansion.

Ah, I shall visit the Fuma mansion shortly. There are indeed
many things I need to report to the leader.
